a>, and <a href="/wiki/Jerry_Goldsmith" title="Jerry Goldsmith">Jerry Goldsmith</a>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Monreal-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Monreal_11-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Carol Monreal, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.speroforum.com/a/GNUHMXSGMH20/75448-Bestselling-author-remains-a-road-warrior-for-human-rights#.VKRwhnuoNS1">"Best-selling Author Remains a Road Warrior for Human Rights,"</a> Spero News, speroforum.com/</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Monreal, "Best-selling Author Remains a Road Warrior for Human Rights." See also: Mariana Barillas, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.speroforum.com/a/DDEKHSOZOI36/75390-Noted-author-Edwin-Black-schools-students-on-the-roots-of-racism#.VKRyRnuoNS0">"Noted Author Edwin Black Schools Students on the Roots of Racism,"</a> Spero News, December 9, 2014; and David Bloom, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.hometownlife.com/story/news/local/birmingham/2014/12/21/award-winning-journalist-talks-ferguson-middle-east/20500165">"Award-winning journalist talks about Ferguson, the Middle East,"</a> Hometown Life.com, December 21, 2014.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-13"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Amol Garg and Valeria Sosa, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.guilfordian.com/news/2014/11/14/human-rights-author-edwin-black-met-with-backlash-and-walk-out/">"Human Rights Author Edwin Black Met with Backlash and Walk-Out,"</a> <i>The Guilfordian,</i> Nov. 14, 2014.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-14"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.worldcat.org/search?q=au%3AEdwin+Black&amp;dbli